# 25. Mandatory BootstrapBlazor Library

Both `web-admin` and `web-tenant` MUST build all UI with the vendored
BootstrapBlazor library at `external/bootstrap-blazor` (referenced via project
reference). Reference docs/demos: https://www.blazor.zone/introduction.

Rules:

- Never add another UI/component library (MudBlazor, Radzen, Ant, etc.).
- Never hand-roll a control when BootstrapBlazor already provides it
  (`Table`, `Select`, `BootstrapInput`, `Card`, `Button`, `Modal`, `Drawer`...).
- Register services in `Program.cs` with `builder.Services.AddBootstrapBlazor();`
  and place `<BootstrapBlazorRoot>` at the app root so `SwalService`,
  `DialogService`, `ToastService`, `MessageService` work.
- This rule applies equally to Admin app and Tenant app.

