# 26. Loading & Spinner Rules

Every async data load MUST show a loading indicator. The user must never see a
blank screen while data is being fetched.

Rules:

- Tables use the built-in `Table` loading. Keep `ShowLoadingInFirstRender="true"`
  (default) and load data inside `OnQueryAsync`; do not pre-render rows.
- For a section or full page load, drive a `_loading` flag and render
  BootstrapBlazor `<Spinner>` (or the shared `AppLoading`) while `true`.
- Use `Skeleton` / `SkeletonTable` for the first paint of cards and lists.
- Always toggle the flag with `try`/`finally` so it is reset even on error.

Loading flag pattern (code-behind):

```csharp
private bool _loading;

protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
{
    _loading = true;
    try
    {
        // Load data from the service layer
        _items = await DataService.GetItemsAsync();
    }
    finally
    {
        // Always clear the loading flag, even when an error is thrown
        _loading = false;
    }
}
```

Spinner markup (.razor):

```razor
@if (_loading)
{
    <div class="app-loading">
        <Spinner Color="Color.Primary" />
        <span class="app-loading-text">Đang tải dữ liệu...</span>
    </div>
}
else
{
    <!-- Loaded content here -->
}
```

Do not:

- Render a table/list without a loading state.
- Block the whole app when only one section is loading.

