# 27. Error Handling & Error Modal Rules

Every call into a service / API from code-behind MUST be wrapped in `try`/`catch`.
Errors must surface to the user in a modal, never be silently swallowed.

Rules:

- Inject `SwalService` and show a blocking error modal with
  `SwalCategory.Error` when an operation fails.
- Use `ToastService` only for non-blocking success/info notifications, not for
  errors that the user must acknowledge.
- Never display raw stack traces to tenant users; log full detail server-side and
  show a short friendly message.
- Centralize the handler (e.g. a shared `ShowErrorAsync` helper) instead of
  duplicating Swal calls in every page.

Inject the service:

```razor
@inject SwalService SwalService
```

Try/catch with error modal:

```csharp
private async Task SaveAsync()
{
    try
    {
        await DataService.SaveAsync(_model);
        // Notify success via toast (non-blocking)
        await ToastService.Success("Thành công", "Đã lưu dữ liệu.");
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        // Surface the failure in a blocking error modal
        await SwalService.Show(new SwalOption
        {
            Category = SwalCategory.Error,
            Title = "Đã xảy ra lỗi",
            Content = ex.Message
        });
    }
}
```

Destructive actions (delete) MUST confirm before executing:

```csharp
private async Task DeleteAsync(Guid id)
{
    var confirmed = await SwalService.ShowModal(new SwalOption
    {
        Category = SwalCategory.Question,
        Title = "Xác nhận xoá",
        Content = "Bạn có chắc muốn xoá bản ghi này?"
    });
    if (!confirmed)
    {
        return;
    }

    try
    {
        await DataService.DeleteAsync(id);
        await ToastService.Success("Đã xoá", "Bản ghi đã được xoá.");
        await ReloadAsync();
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        await SwalService.Show(new SwalOption
        {
            Category = SwalCategory.Error,
            Title = "Xoá thất bại",
            Content = ex.Message
        });
    }
}
```

Do not:

- Leave an empty `catch {}` block.
- Show an error only as plain inline text without a modal for failed actions.

