# 30. Tenant Form UX Rules (Modal / Dialog)

Every create/edit dialog MUST be usable without guessing field meaning.

## Labels

- Wrap each control in `<AppFormField Label="...">` with an explicit Vietnamese label.
- Required fields append `*` via `Required="true"` on `AppFormField`.
- Inside the field, set `ShowLabel="false"` on BootstrapBlazor inputs — the wrapper owns the label.
- Never rely on `DisplayText` alone inside Modal/Dialog (BootstrapBlazor hides labels unless `ShowLabel="true"`).

## Money inputs

- Use `<AppMoneyInput>` / `VnMoney` helper for all currency amounts.
- Format while typing/blur: `.` thousands separator, `,` decimal separator (vi-VN).
- Display money columns with `VnMoney.Format(value)`.

## Boolean fields

- Use BootstrapBlazor `<Checkbox>` (not Switch) for true/false business flags.
- Pair with helper text in `app-form-check-row` when meaning is not obvious.

## Status / enum selects

- Use `<AppStatusSelect>` with colored `app-status-badge` in dropdown and selected value.
- Table status columns MUST render badge spans, not raw enum text.

## Lookup / catalog selects (Select2-style)

- Use `<CustomerLookupSelect>` or `Select` with `ShowSearch="true"`, `IsVirtualize="true"`, `OnQueryAsync` calling API.
- Never preload entire customer lists into static `<Select Items="...">` when count can exceed ~50.

## Kanban boards

- Pipeline boards use horizontal scroll: `display:flex; overflow-x:auto; flex-wrap:nowrap`.
- Columns have fixed width (`flex: 0 0 300px`) and `scroll-snap-align: start`.

## Module menus (tenant)

- Sidebar groups follow `TenantModuleMenus` catalog: CRM, Sales, Purchase, Inventory, ERP, Invoice, Accounting, Payroll, HRM, Attendance, Workflow, Report.
- Show a module group only when `Session.HasModule(code)`.
- Placeholder pages are acceptable until business screens ship.

